WEBVTT

00:02.017 --> 00:03.919
It's, like,
the best one they make,

00:03.921 --> 00:05.954
I just can't get it to work.
I'll figure it out.

00:05.955 --> 00:09.391
It streams HD video straight
to your phone while it's flying.

00:09.393 --> 00:10.792
Nice.

00:10.794 --> 00:13.095
Where were you
when I was single?

00:15.698 --> 00:18.433
Okay, we should leave in
about an hour. You all packed?

00:18.435 --> 00:20.769
Uh, yeah, I just need to throw
in a few last minute things--

00:20.771 --> 00:23.071
you know, makeup,
underwear, clothes.

00:23.740 --> 00:25.641
If your bathroom floor

00:25.643 --> 00:27.643
counts as a carry-on,
you're packed.

00:28.578 --> 00:30.145
Leonard,
have you ever given

00:30.147 --> 00:31.680
a high school
commencement speech before?

00:31.682 --> 00:33.382
Nope. It's pretty exciting.

00:33.384 --> 00:35.784
Aren't you afraid
of being blinded?

00:35.786 --> 00:37.519
How would I be blinded?

00:37.521 --> 00:39.187
At the end of the ceremony,

00:39.189 --> 00:41.923
all the students throw
those pointy hats in the air.

00:43.059 --> 00:44.459
It's all pomp and circumstance

00:44.461 --> 00:47.029
until someone loses an eye.

00:47.031 --> 00:48.664
I'll take my chances.

00:48.666 --> 00:49.865
Fine.

00:49.867 --> 00:51.133
I wonder if they make

00:51.135 --> 00:53.368
"I told you so"
cards in braille.

00:55.104 --> 00:56.938
Look, the problem
with commencement speeches

00:56.940 --> 00:58.907
is that they're boring.

00:58.909 --> 01:01.143
Ooh, do you own
a T-shirt cannon?

01:01.978 --> 01:04.012
Why would he own
a T-shirt cannon?

01:04.013 --> 01:06.114
I don't know. Why do I own one?

01:07.150 --> 01:08.483
I think it's really nice

01:08.485 --> 01:10.018
that you're sharing
this experience with Penny.

01:10.020 --> 01:11.520
Mm, I thought
it'd be fun

01:11.522 --> 01:13.388
to show her my old
stomping grounds.

01:13.390 --> 01:16.858
I even know the exact spot
where they used to stomp me.

01:17.660 --> 01:19.094
Well, now you
get to go back

01:19.096 --> 01:20.462
as a successful
scientist.

01:20.464 --> 01:22.464
With a beautiful girl
on your arm.

01:22.466 --> 01:25.334
And a pointy hat sticking
out of your eyeball.

01:25.336 --> 01:28.970
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:28.972 --> 01:32.307
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:32.309 --> 01:33.942
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:33.944 --> 01:36.478
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:36.480 --> 01:39.147
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪ <i>We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:39.149 --> 01:41.817
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:41.819 --> 01:43.752
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:43.754 --> 01:45.687
♪ <i>Bang!</i> ♪

01:45.688 --> 01:49.688
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 8x22 ♪</font>
